-- 
Allied Technologies, DRDGold, MTN May Be Active in South African Trading

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-04-18T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/allied-technologies-drdgold-mtn-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index declined 839.03, or 2.6
percent, to 31,388.63 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Allied Technologies Ltd. (ALT)  : The maker of television
set-top boxes said it had agreed a 25 percent plus-one-share
transaction with black investors. The shares slipped 2.25 rand,
or 3.9 percent, to 55.15 rand.  Datacentrix Holdings Ltd. (DCT SJ): The computer equipment
distributor reports annual earnings. The shares fell 2 cents, or
0.4 percent, to 4.68 rand.  DRDGold Ltd. (DRD)  : The gold producer is reporting
earnings. The stock retreated 6 cents, or 1.6 percent, to 3.60
rand.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  : Africa’s second-biggest gold
miner may decide by the end of the year whether to expand its
Damang mine in Ghana to a “superpit” after increasing its
stake in the operation,  Chief Executive Officer Nick Holland
said on a conference call. The shares declined 2.18 rand, or 1.8
percent, to 119.82 rand.  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN)  : Africa’s biggest mobile-network
operator said a report that it’s in talks about buying 60
percent of a Zimbabwean mobile-phone company for $600 million is
“mere speculation.” The shares dropped 3.80 rand, or 2.8
percent, to 130.50 rand.  SABMiller Plc (SAB)  : The world’s second-biggest brewer
is issuing a fourth-quarter sales and revenue trading update.
The shares slumped 7.82 rand, or 3.1 percent, to 242.51 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
